============================================================
MANUSCRIPT-READY RESULTS TEXT
============================================================

A total of 4866 adults aged 20 years and older from NHANES 2017-2018 were included, of whom 1189 (24.4%) had normal BMI, 1593 (32.7%) were overweight, and 2084 (42.8%) were obese (Table 1).

Diabetes prevalence was 7.5% (95% CI: 6.1%-9.1%) in the normal group.
Diabetes prevalence was 13.9% (95% CI: 12.3%-15.7%) in the overweight group.
Diabetes prevalence was 19.9% (95% CI: 18.2%-21.6%) in the obese group.

In adjusted logistic regression, obesity was significantly associated with diabetes (OR 4.50, 95% CI: 3.23-6.27, p <0.001). Overweight was also associated with increased odds (OR 2.06, 95% CI: 1.45-2.92, p <0.001) (Figure 2).

